"script": "Slip on noise-cancelling headphones, and the roar of a jet engine just vanishes. But the headphones aren't blocking that sound. They're erasing it. You see, a tiny microphone on each earcup listens to the noise coming at you. Then a chip instantly builds a mirror image of that sound wave, flipped perfectly upside down. And when an upward wave meets a downward wave, they cancel each other into silence. This means your headphones are constantly screaming the exact opposite of the world around you, just so your ears end up hearing nothing at all.",
